A 36-year-old man, Mumeen has been arrested by The Western Nigeria Security Network, code-named Amotekun in Osun State for stealing N1.2million and jewelries from his former landlady.<img src="https://i1.wp.com/instablog9ja.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instablog9ja_20200725_19.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024" />The suspect was arrested on Friday in Osogbo, while wandering around with the properties. According to the corps, the robber claimed to have stolen the N1.2 million since February from his former landlady, but confessed to have spent part of it. He revealed that he was the one taking care of the old woman, which allows him to get access to her room. He said he had kept the money in the bush while shuttling between Ibadan and Osogbo waiting for COVID-19 to end, so he could rent a house and settle down...Also recovered from him were assorted charms and the picture of an expatriate he claimed was brought to him by a client for prayer. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world. By James Ogunnaike The Bishop of the Diocese Ijebu South-west, Church of Nigeria (Anglican Communion) Rt. Rev. Babatunde Ogunbanwo has warned the southwest governors not to allow “sycophants” hijack the operation of the recently launched Western Nigeria Security Network code-named “Operation Amotekun”, The cleric, who lauded the governors for mooting… January 13, 2020 In "News" Governor Seyi Makinde on Tuesday signed the bill establishing the Oyo State Security Network Agency, code-named Operation Amotekun into law. Operation Amotekun was launched on January,9 this year in Ibadan, Oyo state capital by the six south west governors. The Oyo State House of Assembly on February, 24 held a… March 10, 2020 In "News" Some Amotekun personnel during the launching ceremony By Adeola Badru – Ibadan The former President-General of the Yoruba Council of Elders (YCE), 